This file outlines the steps for using the code base provided on this site.

Development Environment  
1. Windows 11 2025 Update (Version 25H2)  
2. Visual Studio 2022  
3. Obtain a "Device Token" from your node operator, which will automatically configure your development environment.

Steps  
1. Download the supplied Fido Provider from https://github.com/Money-2021/VaultedObjects/blob/main/Fido.dll  
   and the Support file from https://github.com/Money-2021/PaymentClient/blob/main/Support  
2. Initialise the Device using the provided authToken  
    Fido.FidoProvider d = new Fido.FidoProvider(authToken, Fido.FidoProvider.TechType.Function);  
   // Register the Device  
   d.Enrol(Enum.GetName(typeof(ProviderType), ProviderType.User));  
   userTokenPath = @"D:\Examples\" + node + @"\" + folder + "\\Token-" + sin + ".json";  
   // Save the Token  
   d.SaveStore(userTokenPath);

3. Use the new Visual Studio Net8.0 MSTest (Microsoft's built-in framework)  
4. Download the UnitTest cases provided  
5. Adapt the supplied code to your local MSTest environment, including configuring your DeviceToken path  
6. Run the supplied UnitTest cases to confirm the code functions correctly

Suggested MSTest flow  
1. UseCase_balance()  
2. UseCase_quote()  
3. UseCase_pay_to_sin()

Notes  
1. A professional developer should typically spend about 30 minutes to complete the first test case  
2. Visual Studio should automatically download or prompt to download all required Net8.0 supporting libraries

Enjoy exploring the new world of global cross-currency payments.
